dataStructure.name: sid.org.tmforum.tip.resource.res.log.tip.nrf.TransmissionDescriptor
dataStructure.description:
This object class is a collection of attributes which are used to define multi-layered transmission parameters and additional info parameters on a resource; e.g., a TP. See R_TMF518_NRF_I_0042 and R_TMF518_NRF_I_0043.

This entity is optional

This entity is extendable

This entity generates Object Creation notifications

This entity generates Object Deletion notifications

This entity generates Object Discovery notifications

This entity generates Attribute Value Change notifications.
dataStructure.label: TransmissionDescriptor

child.name: additionalObjectInfoList
child.description:
This attribute contains additional parameters which can be set and/or retrieved on an object having this Transmission Descriptor (TMD) assigned as (egress or ingress) TMD.

This element is generated from an attribute.

This attribute is optional

This attribute is AVC enabled
child.label: additionalObjectInfoList

child.name: externalRepresentationReference
child.description:
This attribute provides a means to store at the target OS a reference to the external representation of the Transmission Descriptor.

This element is generated from an attribute.

This attribute is optional

This attribute is AVC disabled
child.label: externalRepresentationReference

child.name: transmissionParameterList
child.description:
This attribute contains the layered Transmission Parameters associated with the different layers that are encapsulated within the Transmission Descriptor. Refer to attached supporting document SD1-16_LayeredParameters for details of the currently defined Transmission Parameters

This element is generated from an attribute.

This attribute is optional

This attribute is AVC enabled
child.label: transmissionParameterList
